<br>
Realistically, I will keep the epic sleeves and gloves forever as they have a SC value that is as good as you can get player made. I will probably keep the hauberk, boots, and leggings as well since they have decent SC values. I would plan to replace the hauberk with the Legion hauberk as it is simply UBER beyond anything else (tied with the Dragon Axe) for sheer imbued stats. That leaves just the helm to imbue right off the bat as far as armor is concerned. <br>
<br>
I would make my axe something like +3 axe/+3 parry/+3 axe/+3 parry (a total of +6 axe/+6 parry). <br>
<br>
<br>
Just a note. The best way imo to calculate the value of a piece of gear is not to use the SC value, since items Mythic makes are often not made with SC efficiency in mind. For example, a +6 axe/+6 parry item would have a SC value of 38 but you could craft the same thing for just 30 SC points like I did with the axe. Thus, the best way to calculate value imo is to add up the total points as follows:<br>
<br>
+skill=5*number<br>
+stat=1*number<br>
+resist=2*number<br>
+power=2*number<br>
+hits=number/4<br>
<br>
These are the same values as for SC crafting but without the special imbuing modifiers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=haelfix>Haelfix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/31/02 3:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=380.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> check</span><hr size=1> Check the equipment section of this site, I have a setup that I made up, which gives pretty good returns for a reasonable setup (99qua armor with mild overcharging).<br>
<br>
I get rid of all my armor except for gloves.  The reason I do this, is b/c it seems obvious to me that the main attraction is going to be the reverse procs, moreso than a few extra points for resists.  Not to mention, that I can nearly cap everything with easily attainable items and only mild overcharging.  (the setup lacks in quickness, and about 5 point in parry, but caps weapon at +11 and con/str/dex/hp/resists to within +/- 1 point)<br>
<br>
Of course, jewelcraft is required.  I personally have items atm which can pretty much emulate them, but perhaps others do not.  Either way, I would invest for the long term, since this stuff can get pretty expensive really fast.<br>
<br>
There are a few musthave, easily attainable DF items that I list, which are surprisingly the best maximum imbue items in the game (barring the uberest of the uber items).<br>
<br>
On another note, I am not going to wear my legion hauberk.  The reverse proc is not nice for a chest piece, and I make up for it with a summoner cloak, and a few other uber items. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=380.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=380.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=380.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=380.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.threadControl?topicID=380.topic><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/closethread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=380.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=380.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub3